```

This example sets up the table of contents with custom formatting and includes a `\tableofcontents` command. The `\setcounter{secnumdepth}` and `\setcounter{tocdepth}` commands set the depth of sections to be numbered and included in the table of contents, while the `\renewcommand` commands set the fonts for different elements in the table of contents. Adjust the formatting as needed for your specific document.

